Build a 2d grid which a player can move around in.
Add walls to create a custom shape

Each square is an instance of a class with items, monsters ect.


Level map is a list of sq



Want a dictionary of tiles: key is the coordinate, value is a dictionary of items monsters ect

A level is a dictionary of tile objects with attributes including lists of monsters and items


Want a function that helps build an item/monster

in item __init__ method it uses this function

You will input a template and/or values to create either

For rooms with monsters in use a genetic algorithm to determine monster strength. Simulate fights between players and monsters


Collectible pets that are either from a database or randommly generated. The random ones are then added to the database. Other players can see your pets.

Use a graph to create zones with different properties e.g. difficulty, healing ect. Use spacial partitioning to make rooms. Perhaps cellular
automator to change rooms slightly.

Could insert pre-designed elements into the dungeon in the place of certain sized partitions or within generated rooms.
Certain areas could have more or less pre-designed elemements or cellular automator changed depending on the level of ruin or naturality